    <item>
      <title>New Healing Mechanics</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=8950#M8950</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Cleric soloing, cleric this and cleric mitigation that. The core of the class is healing, so I thought why not start a thread on productivity concerning new healing mechanics or improving them. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I'll start.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Bounce Heal:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A bounce heal mechanic that basically is a targeted heal with an overflow that "bounces" to another target and heals them for the remaining overflow. A mechanic like this could make cross tanking and 2 healers much more efficient to stack. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Splice Heal:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A heal that remains at maximum, but "splits" off to other people in the area and heals them. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Rain Heal:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;That is a spray of healing similar to an aoe "rain" spell for damage. That is anyone within the short range of the rain is healed for so many hit points for perhaps like 3 waves. &lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Tue, 02 Aug 2005 07:27:33 GMT</pubDate>
