      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Vjik wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Cleric soloing, cleric this and cleric mitigation that. The core of the class is healing, so I thought why not start a thread on productivity concerning new healing mechanics or improving them. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I'll start.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Bounce Heal:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A bounce heal mechanic that basically is a targeted heal with an overflow that "bounces" to another target and heals them for the remaining overflow. A mechanic like this could make cross tanking and 2 healers much more efficient to stack. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Splice Heal:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A heal that remains at maximum, but "splits" off to other people in the area and heals them. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Rain Heal:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;That is a spray of healing similar to an aoe "rain" spell for damage. That is anyone within the short range of the rain is healed for so many hit points for perhaps like 3 waves. &lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;How does the "bounce" heal make it better to stack two healers when all it does is heal additional toons if there is overflow?&amp;nbsp; How does that make it good to stack healers?&amp;nbsp; Maybe I am missing the point.&amp;nbsp; Here is how I interpret the "bounce" heal:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;cleric1 starts a complete heal on tank1, the complete heal goes off and actualy completely heals tank1, the "leftover" portion of the heal "bounces" to shaman1 who just canni-ed healing her to 90%, the "bounce" stops.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;OR&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Cleric1 just did DvA, CR is down and he does not have a group heal memmed so he casts Pious Light on tank1 healing him, then it bounces through the group healing everyone from most to least down HP mangaing to get 2/3 of the group back to max HP.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Do I have this wrong?&amp;nbsp; With this ability group heal would no longer be required because a cleric could use a single target heal to heal the group.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The splice heal sounds very similiar to the bounce heal.&amp;nbsp; Please elaborate the difference.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Rain heal would be an interesting addition/change to the group heal line.&amp;nbsp; However, being able to fully utilize a group heal if the entire group is not in range though would make it over-powered.&amp;nbsp; That's the risk you take when you use a group heal - if all members are damaged and in range group heal is VERY mana efficient but if one or two are oor then the efficiency drops radically.&amp;nbsp; Being able to "focus" a group heal on the targets that are in range upsets the balance IMO.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;It appears to me that you want to get rid of the need to mem a group heal spell :smileywink:.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Tue, 02 Aug 2005 14:15:06 GMT</pubDate>
