    <item>
      <title>Re: New Healing Mechanics</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=8955#M8955</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Bounce heal's limitation is on the overflow itself, so let's say you heal for 4k. You heal the tank for 3.5k and the rest of the heal "bounces" to another person in the nearby area to heal them for 500. A play on the overheal mechanic people have been rallying for that would be less buff dependant and probably less coding involved to work.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Splice mechanics in other games basically work like this, the cast is more expensive but still slightly less than casting 2-3 heals and has the ability to be cast faster than those 2 heals as well. A splice mechanic's weakness is in it's randomness to choose the other targets and being weaker than a direct heal. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Rain heal could have a few weakensses. Firstly, the amount healed each round of "rain" spliced over 3 rounds. Secondly, the foci not altering it. Thirdly the range itself as it "rains." So the cleric would have to be close to other people to have her rains go off for full effect. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
